    "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::browse_logs_loose_local_mutability": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::browse_logs_loose_local_mutability",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "browse-logs handler uses `let` + implicit any[] for variables that are never reassigned, slightly muddying the locally-scoped state intent",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "src/routes/api/browse-logs/+server.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Line ~15: `let whereConditions = [];` \u2014 implicit any[] (lost the SQL[] type) and the array is only ever .push()'d into, never reassigned.",
          "Line ~30: `let query = getRaidDb().select({\u2026})\u2026orderBy(\u2026);` declared with `let` but immediately awaited at `const compositionsData = await query;` with no reassignment in between.",
          "Both shapes contrast with the rest of the file (and the rest of src/lib/) which use const + explicit array typing for builder lists."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Change to `const whereConditions: SQL[] = [];` (importing SQL from drizzle-orm) and `const query = getRaidDb().select(\u2026)\u2026orderBy(\u2026);`. Pure local cleanup; no behavior change.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "d8b3e714"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-04-26T11:21:47+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-04-26T11:21:47+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "work_item_kind": "review_defect",
      "issue_kind": "review_defect",
      "origin": "review_import",
      "lang": "typescript",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::current_state_unneeded_iife_indirection": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::current_state_unneeded_iife_indirection",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "currentState.saveToAPI wraps its fetch in a `const doSave = async () => {\u2026}; doSave();` IIFE for no reason",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/data/currentState.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "saveToAPI body declares an inner `doSave` async arrow that does the fetch + error logging, then immediately invokes it without awaiting.",
          "There are no other callers of `doSave`, no parameters captured beyond `urlParams` (which is already in scope), and no try/catch outside the inner arrow.",
          "The same fire-and-forget effect can be expressed by `void (async () => {\u2026})();` inline, or by making saveToAPI itself the async function and letting callers ignore the promise \u2014 the wrapper adds a layer of nested indentation without isolating anything."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Inline the body of `doSave` directly into saveToAPI (still fire-and-forget) or hoist it to a module-level `async function postCurrentState(urlParams)` helper. Removes one frame of indentation and matches the directness of every other store helper in the file.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "f4f5aa77"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-04-26T11:21:47+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-04-26T11:21:47+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "work_item_kind": "review_defect",
      "issue_kind": "review_defect",
      "origin": "review_import",
      "lang": "typescript",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::score_formula_recomputed_lookup_and_dead_tail": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::score_formula_recomputed_lookup_and_dead_tail",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "scoreFormula rebuilds an affix-breakpoint lookup on every call, and computeRunLevelsForScore has an unreachable trailing return",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/calculations/keystoneCalculations.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Inside scoreFormula(), `const affixBreakpoints: Record<number, number> = Object.fromEntries(KEYSTONE_SCORING.AFFIX_BREAKPOINT_LEVELS.map(level => [level, KEYSTONE_SCORING.AFFIX_BREAKPOINT_BONUS]));` is rebuilt every call from a frozen-shape constant.",
          "computeRunLevelsForScore() has an `if (targetScore >= FAST_PATH_TARGET) {\u2026always returns inside loop or falls through} else {\u2026always returns}` followed by a tail `return result;` that is unreachable except when the fast-path loop completes without finding a hit (i.e. MAX_LEVEL_SEARCH exhausted) \u2014 that fallback is silent and deserves either a comment or an explicit safeguard."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Hoist the lookup to a module-level constant (or replace the Record with `KEYSTONE_SCORING.AFFIX_BREAKPOINT_LEVELS.includes(nextLevel)` since the bonus is the same for every breakpoint). For computeRunLevelsForScore, comment the fast-path-exhaustion fallthrough explicitly so the trailing `return result;` reads as intentional rather than vestigial.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "cb316451"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
